          class="- topic/topic ">
		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">25.100</ph> Scope of subpart.</title>
		    <body class="- topic/body ">
			      <ol id="d1593e13" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1607e17" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            This subpart implements-</p>
					          <ol id="d1593e23" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1607e27" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                
								                <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S.C. chapter 83</xref>, Buy American;</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1607e39" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Executive Order 10582, December 17, 1954; and</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1607e48" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(3)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                Waiver of the component test of the Buy American statute for acquisition of commercially available off-the-shelf (COTS) items in accordance with <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                              format="html"
                              scope="external"
                              class="- topic/xref ">41 U.S .C 1907</xref>.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1607e62" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            It applies to supplies acquired for use in the United States, including supplies acquired under contracts set aside for small business concerns, if-</p>
					          <ol id="d1593e68" class="- topic/ol ">
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1607e72" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(1)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The supply contract exceeds the micro-purchase threshold; or</p>
						            </li>
						            <li class="- topic/li ">
							              <p id="d1607e81" class="- topic/p ">
                        <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(2)</ph>
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
                        
								                The supply portion of a contract for services that involves the furnishing of supplies (<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">e.g.</i>, lease) exceeds the micro-purchase threshold.</p>
						            </li>
					          </ol>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
